cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with a geometric optimization problem (terrain guarding) and proposes a discretization technique to solve it. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and filtering techniques, which are common topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also formulates the problem as an Integer Linear Program (IP), which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
